1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:17,000
Season 4 is going to be the biggest update we have ever made to Diablo 4 since it has launched.

2
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Our focus on Season 4 is to really make a lot of evergreen updates to the core systems of Diablo 4.

3
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:37,000
In Season 4, we're ramping the intensity across the seasonal and eternal realms through a collection of new activities aimed at ensuring the moment-to-moment gameplay experience is as exciting and rewarding when HAL comes to Sanctuary.

4
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Season 4 item changes are some of the biggest changes we've made to Diablo 4 thus far.

5
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:59,000
We've never done anything like this. We are fundamentally changing how you engage with items, how you upgrade them, and along the way, solving a lot of things that we've seen continually from our community that we agree with are pain points of our existing item system right now.

6
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:05,000
So in this new itemization system, we're focusing on narrowing down the scope of the base affixes.

7
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:16,000
They're going to be a lot simpler, they're going to be fewer in number, so you can much more easily parse whether this item is useful for you, and if it is, then you can take it and further upgrade it and customize it to your own specific build.

8
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:24,000
Tempering is a new system that allows you to really customize the gear that you find.

9
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:34,000
In order to temper, you will need to go to the blacksmith and then choose the recipe that you wish to temper from, and then a random affix from that recipe will be attached onto your gear.

10
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:38,000
Tempering recipes can be found from almost all of the content throughout Sanctuaries.

11
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:43,000
So you will actually be looking for tempering recipes that go directly with what you're envisioning.

12
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:46,000
Maybe you're thinking, I'm going to play a Frost Sorceress.

13
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:57,000
There are also going to be recipes that are more generic and maybe are just generally good for the Sorceress, but you'll be able to choose which one you think is going to be most powerful with the build you're making for your class.

14
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:08,000
We're making a pretty radical change to the Codex of Power in this season, based again on the feedback that has been coming from our players.

15
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:18,000
Now, every single legendary in the game will be entered into your Codex of Power so that you can continually imprint the best possible version of that legendary onto your gear.

16
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:25,000
So going forward, there will no longer be carrying around all of these Aspect Crystals in your inventory. It's all going to be in the Codex of Power.

17
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:36,000
So part of the final system that we have is going to be greater affixes. What's a greater affix?

18
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:43,000
Well, we want to keep it compelling that there are some drops that are even better than the others when you're trying to get the perfect build at endgame.

19
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:54,000
Because of this, in World Tier 4 and only in World Tier 4, when an Ancestral Legendary item drops, there's a chance the affixes on it can roll as greater affixes.

20
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:58,000
These will roll with bigger values that are normally available for that affix.

21
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:07,000
